## 4. System Description

### 4.1 Purpose and Function

The AWS Security Lab is a personally developed cloud security environment designed to demonstrate practical implementation of NIST 800-53 security controls in an AWS cloud infrastructure. The system provides a realistic representation of a secured cloud environment aligned to DoD/Federal security requirements.

The system serves the following functions:
- Demonstrate segmented cloud network architecture with enforced boundary protection
- Implement and document least-privilege identity and access management
- Provide a platform for continuous monitoring using AWS-native security services
- Produce RMF-aligned documentation artifacts including SSPs, POA&Ms, and SARs

