## 5. System Environment and Architecture

### 5.1 Network Architecture

The system operates within a dedicated AWS VPC (10.0.0.0/16) in the us-east-1 region. The network is segmented into public and private subnets with enforced routing boundaries.

```
Internet
    │
    ▼
Internet Gateway
    │
    ▼
Public Subnet (10.0.1.0/24)     ← ALB / Future public-facing resources
    │
    │  (No direct path to private subnet — Security Group controlled)
    │
Private Subnet (10.0.2.0/24)    ← EC2 compute resources
    │
    ▼
SSM VPC Endpoint                ← Remote access without internet exposure
```

### 5.2 Authorization Boundary

The authorization boundary encompasses all AWS resources provisioned within the defined VPC, including:
- All EC2 instances and associated EBS volumes
- All VPC networking components (subnets, route tables, security groups, IGW)
- All IAM roles and policies associated with the system
- All logging and monitoring services (CloudTrail, GuardDuty, Security Hub, Inspector, Config)
- All S3 buckets used for log storage

AWS platform-level infrastructure (hypervisor, physical hardware, global network) is outside the authorization boundary and is covered under the AWS FedRAMP authorization.

